title: McCallie School vs. Baylor School
text: Chattanooga, TN (WDEF) - Seems like a few people want to check out this game. 2nd Quarter, Baylor is already up 7 - 0 and they punch it in again. Ryan Parker from 2 yards out, it's 14 - 0. Following a McCallie fumble, Baylor is back in business, it's Ryan Parker again. This time he goes in from 11 yards out. Now it's 21 - 0. Later in the quarter, McCallie at the Baylor 5, Gage Upshaw blows up the play in the backfield. McCallie fumbles, and Tyree Toliver recovers for Baylor. 3 seconds before halftime. Baylor wants to tack on a field goal. Victor Ulmo nails it from 42 yards out. 24 - 0 Baylor at the half. 2nd half, McCallie trying to find their mojo. Robert Riddle to pass, this isn't mojo.This is a turnover. Picked off by #2 Brandon Harris, and he returned it to the 35. Baylor gets it to the 1, where they give it to the Rhino, Ryan Parker, that touchdown makes it 31 - 0. End of the 3rd, McCallie finally gets on the board. Riddle to Giovanni Hightower, a 7 yard score. Two point try made it 31 - 8. Baylor goes on to win 38 - 14.
